Would you look at the residents.

94
00:04:49,056 --> 00:04:53,408
Big, snazzy residents. Standing
around, playing with housewares.

95
00:04:54,695 --> 00:04:57,028
Turn a blind eye, the
soup tureen's yours.

96
00:05:01,117 --> 00:05:03,001
Four! Take this Mix... Hey!

97
00:05:03,103 --> 00:05:07,756
Take the Mixmaster and all
this crap and put in my locker.

98
00:05:10,143 --> 00:05:13,044
Carnage in the pit.
My day's improving.

99
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,266
Follow.

100
00:05:19,836 --> 00:05:22,337
- We're not gonna round?
- Carnage trumps rounds.

101
00:05:22,439 --> 00:05:24,923
Write that down.
Carnage trumps rounds.

102
00:05:26,009 --> 00:05:28,076
- Callie.
- Oh, hey. I know, I know.

103
00:05:28,178 --> 00:05:30,678
I never made it home. Got
swamped with paperwork

104
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:33,448
and fell asleep
in an on-call room.

105
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:35,216
I need to talk when
you have time.

106
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,484
I have no time.

107
00:05:36,586 --> 00:05:38,330
This chief resident
thing is kicking my ass.

108
00:05:38,354 --> 00:05:42,306
- Later then? Tonight when we're alone.
- Is it serious?

109
00:05:42,409 --> 00:05:43,975
What do we got?

110
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:47,178
Uh, gas main blew in a
building. Five injured. Some badly.

111
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,231
Excellent. Horrible.
It's horrible. Sad.

112
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:56,905
Marla Kristler, 34-year-old female,
abdomen blown out, skull fracture,

113
00:05:57,007 --> 00:05:59,552
third-degree burns over
40 percent of her body.

114
00:05:59,576 --> 00:06:01,309
OK, I got this. Open OR Two.

115
00:06:01,411 --> 00:06:03,678
Page Dr. Shepherd.
Torres, triage the rest.

116
00:06:03,781 --> 00:06:05,625
Yes. Yang, you're
with the chief.

117
00:06:05,649 --> 00:06:07,315
Thank you. One,
Four, come with me.

118
00:06:07,417 --> 00:06:10,551
- What about us?
- Uh, go help Bailey
in the clinic.

119
00:06:15,241 --> 00:06:18,009
My wife came in another
ambulance. Is she here?

120
00:06:18,111 --> 00:06:21,612
- Straight to surgery. Are you injured?
- No. My son.

121
00:06:21,714 --> 00:06:24,215
Eighteen months old.
Contusion, possible head injury.

122
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:25,983
BP and pulse are elevated.

123
00:06:26,086 --> 00:06:28,214
- Everything's
going to be OK, baby.
- Karev!

124
00:06:28,238 --> 00:06:30,784
- I'm supposed
to be on plastics.
- I'll take it.

125
00:06:30,808 --> 00:06:36,227
- Karev. You're
with the Kristlers.
- What about me?

126
00:06:36,329 --> 00:06:37,740
Were you up late last night?

127
00:06:37,764 --> 00:06:40,398
You look tired. Perhaps
you should sit this out.

128
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,266
I'm fine. Not up late.

129
00:06:42,368 --> 00:06:46,104
Went to bed early.
Early and alone.

130
00:06:46,206 --> 00:06:48,406
- Hello, Mr...
- Roche. Archie Roche.

131
00:06:48,508 --> 00:06:51,609
"Age 60, second, third-degree
burns, chest, upper abdomen,

132
00:06:51,711 --> 00:06:53,645
facial contusions and fracture."

133
00:06:53,747 --> 00:06:57,949
Reading the sports section, next
I'm looking up at a hole in the ceiling

134
00:06:58,051 --> 00:07:00,969
- in Dave and Marla's apartment.
- Burns should be débrided.

135
00:07:01,088 --> 00:07:03,939
We'll do a trauma series
and shoulder films. Stevens.

136
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:05,601
- Got it.
- Where's your pain?

137
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:08,527
Just promise me you'll take
care of Marla and the baby.

138
00:07:08,629 --> 00:07:12,246
- Are they your family, sir?
- They might as well be.

139
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:14,315
How close to the
explosion was he?

140
00:07:14,417 --> 00:07:18,352
We were in the living room.
His mom was in the kitchen and...

141
00:07:18,454 --> 00:07:21,639
- Did the gas line blow?
- I think it was the stove.

142
00:07:21,741 --> 00:07:23,358
Gonna run some
tests on the baby.

143
00:07:23,459 --> 00:07:27,012
Karev, I'm going into surgery
with the chief. Keep me posted.

144
00:07:27,114 --> 00:07:28,329
Marla and David are friends.

145
00:07:28,431 --> 00:07:31,299
I was just leaving when
the kitchen blew up.

146
00:07:31,401 --> 00:07:33,985
The blast knocked
me into a wall.

147
00:07:35,355 --> 00:07:37,555
Have you seen this?

148
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:40,625
Grim. You guys look grim.

149
00:07:40,727 --> 00:07:44,696
Clark, we need to get a CT
just to check for internal bleeding.

150
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:48,533
Internal bleeding? I
was on my way to work.

151
00:07:51,554 --> 00:07:54,906
I need a resident to help me in
the clinic to oversee the new interns

152
00:07:55,008 --> 00:07:58,743
- while I'm working
on this patient.
- I'm sorry. I can't help.

153
00:07:58,845 --> 00:08:02,113
- You can't help?
- The clinic
is voluntary, Bailey.

154
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:05,128
I'm not gonna force residents
with this much going on.

155
00:08:05,152 --> 00:08:07,712
You can have as many
interns as you need.

156
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,540
Tell Kent he's got to
find himself another OR.

157
00:08:12,642 --> 00:08:14,291
- The chief's taking his.
- OK.

158
00:08:14,394 --> 00:08:16,327
- Waffle maker.
- We covered this.

159
00:08:16,429 --> 00:08:19,764
- But now I got
something you want.
- Yeah? What?

160
00:08:24,488 --> 00:08:27,455
Hello. I'm Jane Burke.

161
00:08:27,557 --> 00:08:29,735
Dr. Burke's mother.
Nice to see you.

162
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:32,093
I'm looking for a
Dr. Cristina Yang.

163
00:08:32,195 --> 00:08:34,679
Yang, Yang. Let
me see. Dr. Yang...

164
00:08:34,781 --> 00:08:38,111
I'll page her. But I
think she's in surgery.

165
00:08:38,135 --> 00:08:39,934
I'll wait.

166
00:08:42,856 --> 00:08:44,756
- Waffle maker?
- Fine.

167
00:08:55,569 --> 00:08:57,536
- Hey. What's the 911?
- Mama is here.

168
00:08:57,638 --> 00:08:59,716
I'm working with Callie.
Got to find George.

169
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:02,924
- Your mother? What?
- Not my mother. Mama is here.

170
00:09:03,026 --> 00:09:05,093
- George? He's your intern.
- Burke's mom.

171
00:09:05,195 --> 00:09:07,445
Make the synapses
fire more quickly.

172
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:09,697
I was with a patient.
I'd be happy to go back.

173
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,260
- No, help.
- I'll help.

174
00:09:11,284 --> 00:09:13,145
For Mixmaster and
George's location.

175
00:09:13,169 --> 00:09:14,652
Yang, you scrubbing in?

176
00:09:14,737 --> 00:09:16,204
Yes, sir. Absolutely.

177
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:19,774
Just get rid of
her, OK? Politely.

178
00:09:20,810 --> 00:09:22,426
- What?
- George!

179
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:26,764
Hey. Hey. It's OK. Brian,
I'm here. It's OK, sweetheart.

180
00:09:26,866 --> 00:09:28,866
Brian, stop crying,
baby. I can't think.

181
00:09:28,968 --> 00:09:32,737
- Why won't he stop crying?
- Hey there, Brian.

182
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:35,823
You're a big boy.
Do you work out?

183
00:09:35,925 --> 00:09:39,560
You take care of yourself.

184
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:44,365
Dr. Karev. CT results.
Should I page Shepherd?

185
00:09:44,467 --> 00:09:47,568
- He's in surgery. Let me take a look.
- What do you see?

186
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:50,538
- There's nothing acute.
- Nothing? So he's
going to be OK?

187
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:54,309
Yeah, I'm gonna... I need to
run a couple more tests, OK?

188
00:09:57,414 --> 00:10:00,827
Schedule an MRI and have the
lab run a tox screen on Brian's blood.

189
00:10:00,851 --> 00:10:04,936
- Why?
- I said so, Nancy Drew. Just do it.

190
00:10:06,823 --> 00:10:09,190
Rooms one and seven are private

191
00:10:09,292 --> 00:10:12,093
and should be used for
conversations with patients,

192
00:10:12,195 --> 00:10:15,730
not for closed door socializing.
All carts are set up the same.

193
00:10:15,832 --> 00:10:19,951
- Memorize where everything is.
- Will we do procedures
on our own?

194
00:10:21,171 --> 00:10:24,622
No, you are interns. You
are in charge of nothing.

195
00:10:24,724 --> 00:10:29,009
All procedures will be discussed
and overseen by an upper level,

196
00:10:29,112 --> 00:10:31,562
all charts will be signed
out by an upper level,

197
00:10:31,664 --> 00:10:34,732
and all patients will be looked
at by someone other than you!

198
00:10:34,834 --> 00:10:36,662
And what if...? Ooh! I'm sorry.

199
00:10:36,686 --> 00:10:40,321
I... Sorry. What if
we can't find anyone?

200
00:10:43,343 --> 00:10:44,943
Mrs. Burke!

201
00:10:45,045 --> 00:10:48,746
What a surprise to see you
here. Are you visiting someone?

202
00:10:48,849 --> 00:10:53,601
- You're the maid of honor. Miss Grey.
- That's me.

203
00:10:53,703 --> 00:10:57,171
When you stood up in front of
Preston's friends and loved ones

204
00:10:57,274 --> 00:11:02,343
and you said, "It's over,
it's over, it's so over,"

205
00:11:02,445 --> 00:11:06,847
were you trying to smash
the hopes of the best man

206
00:11:06,949 --> 00:11:08,949
or were you just
trying to be funny?

207
00:11:10,871 --> 00:11:13,171
- I...
- Because making light

208
00:11:13,273 --> 00:11:16,941
of that situation
would be inappropriate.

209
00:11:17,044 --> 00:11:19,644
And to use that moment

210
00:11:19,746 --> 00:11:23,314
to send a message
to your boyfriend,

211
00:11:23,417 --> 00:11:25,834
well, that's selfish.

212
00:11:27,737 --> 00:11:30,572
So were you being inappropriate

213
00:11:30,673 --> 00:11:33,124
or were you being selfish?

214
00:11:33,226 --> 00:11:37,345
I... am...

215
00:11:37,447 --> 00:11:40,765
I apologize for that,
Mrs. Mama. Ma'am.

216
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:46,571
I'm just gonna go. OK.

217
00:11:47,424 --> 00:11:49,857
- Miss Grey?
- Yes, ma'am.

218
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:52,627
When you report
back to Cristina,

219
00:11:52,729 --> 00:11:55,796
would you tell her, please,
that I am waiting for her?

220
00:11:55,898 --> 00:11:59,000
And that I will
continue to wait for her.

221
00:11:59,102 --> 00:12:01,086
Yes, ma'am.

222
00:12:04,657 --> 00:12:09,276
- Oh! Sorry. Sorry.
- Any news on Marla?

223
00:12:10,396 --> 00:12:11,796
My neighbor?

224
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:15,199
I promise as soon as I hear
something, I'll give you an update.

225
00:12:19,338 --> 00:12:23,607
Crap! Sorry. I'm really
sorry. Really sorry.

226
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:27,111
Three-part proximal
humerus fracture.

227
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:29,864
Percutaneous reduction
and internal fixation.

228
00:12:29,966 --> 00:12:34,051
That boy of theirs,
Brian. Gorgeous.

229
00:12:34,154 --> 00:12:37,354
And sometimes
they're not. The kids.

230
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:41,425
Sometimes they're ugly.
