350
00:19:12,435 --> 00:19:14,719
I've never touched the stuff.

351
00:19:14,821 --> 00:19:16,637
What's going on?

352
00:19:16,739 --> 00:19:20,774
The Kristlers had a meth lab in their
apartment. It caused the explosion.

353
00:19:20,893 --> 00:19:25,529
Marla and Dave had a
drug lab in their apartment?

354
00:19:25,631 --> 00:19:30,017
No. Impossible. Absolutely not.

355
00:19:30,119 --> 00:19:32,987
I've known those
two for five years.

356
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:38,458
We've gone on picnics, to
ball games. I baby-sit for them.

357
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:45,899
I baby-sit for drug dealers?

358
00:19:51,123 --> 00:19:52,668
- O'Malley!
- What happened?

359
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:54,458
- He coded.
- He coded?

360
00:19:54,561 --> 00:19:56,922
Coded. Out of nowhere.
Heart stopped, coded.

361
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:59,213
- Probably a drug addict.
- What?

362
00:19:59,315 --> 00:20:01,482
I came to tell you.
That fire that he was in?

363
00:20:01,584 --> 00:20:04,919
It was a meth lab explosion.
He could have cardiomyopathy.

364
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:09,673
- That would explain it.
- It's a miracle
I got him back.

365
00:20:09,775 --> 00:20:13,744
- You ran the code? Where's Grey?
- She's covering in the clinic.

366
00:20:15,597 --> 00:20:18,532
What is she doing in the
clinic? I told you to take interns.

367
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,834
I didn't want interns.

368
00:20:26,575 --> 00:20:28,643
Sorry about that.

369
00:20:28,745 --> 00:20:33,114
Some things, O'Malley, some
things just don't need to be told.

370
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:40,321
- How about here? Does it hurt here?
- Weird.

371
00:20:40,423 --> 00:20:43,707
- It feels weird?
- No, that lady
is staring at me.

372
00:20:43,810 --> 00:20:45,676
Or my fat.

373
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:48,812
Don't worry, she's
staring at me.

374
00:20:50,599 --> 00:20:52,599
I'll be right back, OK?

375
00:20:53,903 --> 00:20:56,236
- Well?
- How'd surgery go
on the mom?

376
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:59,201
She'll live. That's not the
mom I'm worried about.

377
00:20:59,225 --> 00:21:03,460
I tried. I tried. Mama is not
budging. And she is very scary.

378
00:21:03,562 --> 00:21:05,046
Yeah, obviously.

379
00:21:05,148 --> 00:21:07,798
What does she want?
Did Burke send her?

380
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:10,484
I don't know. I
mean, you have to go.

381
00:21:10,586 --> 00:21:12,286
You have to go deal with Mama.

382
00:21:12,388 --> 00:21:15,872
Just go get it over with. Come
back and tell me all about it

383
00:21:15,975 --> 00:21:17,975
because I could
use a pick-me-up.

384
00:21:18,077 --> 00:21:20,538
Mama Showdown is
not for your enjoyment.

385
00:21:20,562 --> 00:21:24,849
Besides, my patient is stable and
until I'm paged I'm gonna stay right here.

386
00:21:24,951 --> 00:21:27,918
OK, she keeps staring
